Problem occurs when some decorator from JDT/UI asks a question which triggered
classpath initialization (during which we take the workspace lock eagerly).

Platform-ui locked on its own decoration rule; then we want to lock on
workspace, and our rule get blamed for containment issues.

Suspecting the logic in platform layer to be invalid:
ThreadJob#push(ISchedulingRule) should not check for:
//check for containment last because we don't want to fail again on endRule
if (baseRule != null && rule != null && !baseRule.contains(rule))
  illegalPush(rule, baseRule);
}

but rather:

//check for containment last because we don't want to fail again on endRule
if (baseRule != null && rule != null && rule.contains(baseRule))
  illegalPush(rule, baseRule);
}

This would allow disjoint locks to perform whithout causing any grief.
